<p>A U.S. Democratic lawmaker, Eugene Vindman—who served on President Trump’s National Security Council in his first term—urged the White House to release a transcript of a 2019 call between Trump and Saudi Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman following Jamal Khashoggi’s killing [al-monitor.com#1][scmp.com#1][newarab.com#1]. Speaking alongside Khashoggi’s widow, Hanan Elatr Khashoggi, at a news conference, Vindman called the call shocking and said the public should know its contents [al-monitor.com#1][scmp.com#1][japantoday.com#1]. Vindman, who reviewed confidential telephone calls as part of his NSC work, added that “the receipts will raise serious questions” [straitstimes.com#1][al-monitor.com#1].</p><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Call details: Vindman is seeking release of a transcript of a 2019 phone call between President Trump and Saudi Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman, which he described as shocking [al-monitor.com#1][scmp.com#1][newarab.com#1]</li><li>NSC background: He served on the National Security Council during Trump’s first term and reviewed confidential telephone calls [straitstimes.com#1][al-monitor.com#1]</li><li>Widow’s appeal: Hanan Elatr Khashoggi joined the news conference, supporting the call for transparency about the 2019 conversation [al-monitor.com#1][scmp.com#1][japantoday.com#1]</li><li>Context: The 2019 call occurred after journalist Jamal Khashoggi was killed in 2018, a case that drew global attention [al-monitor.com#1][newarab.com#1][common]</li><li>Public interest: Vindman argued that “the receipts will raise serious questions,” saying the American public and Khashoggi’s family should know what was discussed [al-monitor.com#1][scmp.com#1]</li></ul><blockquote>The Khashoggi family and the American people deserve to know what was in that call... the receipts will raise serious questions, - Eugene Vindman</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Eugene Vindman: Argues the 2019 Trump–Saudi call was shocking and that releasing the transcript is in the public interest [al-monitor.com#1][scmp.com#1] (<a href='https://www.al-monitor.com/originals/2025/11/democrat-demands-release-shocking-trump-saudi-call-2019-after-khashoggis-death'>Al-Monitor (Reuters); South China Morning Post</a>)</li><li>Hanan Elatr Khashoggi: Supports releasing the transcript to bring more transparency surrounding her late husband’s case [scmp.com#1][japantoday.com#1] (<a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/world/united-states-canada/article/3333765/khashoggis-widow-and-democrats-demand-release-shocking-trump-saudi-call'>South China Morning Post; Japan Today (Reuters)</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/united-states/democrat-demands-release-of-shocking-trump-saudi-call-from-2019-after-khashoggis-death'>Democrat demands release of ‘shocking’ Trump-Saudi call from 2019 after Khashoggi’s death</a> - straitstimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.newarab.com/news/democrat-demands-release-trump-saudi-call-after-khashoggis-death'>Democrat demands release of Trump-Saudi call after Khashoggi&#x27;s death</a> - newarab.com</li><li><a href='https://www.al-monitor.com/originals/2025/11/democrat-demands-release-shocking-trump-saudi-call-2019-after-khashoggis-death'>Democrat demands release of &#x27;shocking&#x27; Trump-Saudi call from 2019 after Khashoggi&#x27;s death</a> - al-monitor.com</li><li><a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/world/united-states-canada/article/3333765/khashoggis-widow-and-democrats-demand-release-shocking-trump-saudi-call'>Khashoggi’s widow and Democrats demand release of ‘shocking’ Trump-Saudi call</a> - scmp.com</li><li><a href='https://japantoday.com/category/world/kashoggi%27s-widow-and-democrats-demand-release-of-a-call-transcript-with-trump-and-saudi-crown-prince'>Khashoggi&#x27;s widow and Democrats demand release of call transcript with Trump and Saudi crown prince</a> - japantoday.com</li></ul>